{"name": "motmot-flymovieformat", "metadata": {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat", "version": "1.10", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://code.astraw.com/projects/motmot/fly-movie-format.html", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "support for .fmf (fly movie format) files", "upload_time": 1586342583}, "documentation": ["# motmot.FlyMovieFormat\n\n[![build](https://github.com/motmot/FlyMovieFormat/workflows/build-and-test/badge.svg?branch=master)](https://github.com/motmot/FlyMovieFormat/actions?query=branch%3Amaster)\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/motmot.FlyMovieFormat.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/motmot.FlyMovieFormat)\n\nFly movie format (or .fmf) files are a simple, uncompressed video format for\nstoring data from digital video cameras. A fixed-size per frame means that\nrandom access is extremely fast, and a variety of formats (e.g. MONO8, YUV422)\nare supported.\n\nThis is a subpackage of the motmot family of digital image utilities."], "modules": [{"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.filename", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.fly_movie", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.n_frames", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.timestamps", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.diff", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "scripts.plot_timestamps.zero_offset_msec", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "scripts.fmf_subtract_frame", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "scripts.fmf_subtract_frame.doit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "input_fname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "subtract_frame", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "stop", "type":