, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.tests.TestExporterPlugins.test_plugins", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.images2fmf", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.images2fmf.images2fmf", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "input_filenames", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "out_fname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "version", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["convert a series of images into an .fmf file\n\narguments\n---------\n\ninput_filenames: a list of strings of filenames ['filename1.png','filename2.png']\nout_fname: an output filename for the resulting .fmf movie\nversion: a version specifier for the output .fmf\n\nnotes\n-----\n\nThe input images must be have the same width, height and mode. The\norder in which they are specified is the order saved into the new\n.fmf movie. Timestamps are generated from framenumbers starting\nfrom zero."]}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.images2fmf.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.images2fmf.mode2format", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.this_directory", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat", "documentation": ["This module contains code to read and write FlyMovieFormat\nfiles, which end with extension .fmf.\n\nUsers may like to use these classes:\n\n> - {class}`~motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovie` : read .fmf files\n> - {class}`~motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieSaver` : write .fmf files\n\nThe following Exception types may sometimes be raised:\n\n> - {class}`~motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.NoMoreFramesException` :\n> - {class}`~motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.InvalidMovieFileException` :\n\n# Reading an .fmf from Python\n\nIn Python accessing frames from an .fmf files is as easy as:\n\n```\nimport motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat as FMF\nimport sys\n\nfname = sys.argv[1]\nfmf = FMF.FlyMovie(fname)\nfor frame_number in range(10):\n    frame,timestamp = fmf.get_frame(frame_number)\n```\n\n# Writing an .fmf in Python\n\nWriting frames to an .fmf file is also easy:\n\n```\nimport motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat as FMF\nimport sys\nimport numpy as np\n\nfname = sys.argv[1]\nfmf_saver = FMF.FlyMovieSaver(fname)\n\nwidth, height = 640,480\nfor i in range(10):\n    fake_image = np.zeros( (height,width), dtype=np.uint8)\n    fake_timestamp = 0.0\n    fmf_saver.add_frame(fake_image,fake_timestamp)\n\nfmf_saver.close()\n```\n\n# Module documentation\n", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.format2bpp_func", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "format", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.mmap_flymovie", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["map .fmf file to RAM\n\nNote: make mmap does not currently work with RGB images.\n\nNote: to map a 4 GB or larger file to RAM, a 64 bit computer is\nrequired."]}], "variables": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.VERSION_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FORMAT_LEN_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.BITS_PER_PIXEL_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FRAMESIZE_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.CHUNKSIZE_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.N_FRAME_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.TIMESTAMP_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": ["XXX struct.pack('<d',nan) dies"]}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.CHUNK_N_FRAME_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.CHUNK_TIMESTAMP_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": ["XXX struct.pack('<d',nan) dies"]}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.CHUNK_DATASIZE_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.format2bpp", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.NoMoreFramesException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A frame was requested, but no more frames exist"]}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.InvalidMovieFileException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["The file is not a valid movie file"]}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovie", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovie.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "check_integrity", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "motmot.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovieFormat.FlyMovie.compute_n_frames_from_file_size", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "ty